Mozambique is regularly affected by natural disasters, including floods, drought and cyclones. Cyclones and floods are particularly common during the rainy season (November-April).
Tropical Storm Guambe is forecast to bring hazardous sea and weather conditions to Inhambane province and other parts of Southern Mozambique from 18 February 2021. Floods and landslides are likely in affected areas. Monitor local reports and international weather updates from the World Meteorological Organisation, check your routes before travelling around the country and follow the advice of the local authorities.
